The paper deals with the problem of computing a spanning tree with low crossing number for a set of points in $\Re^d$, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithm presented is based on linear programming, which is a common technique in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the more general problem of building a spanning tree for a set system with bounded \VC dimension, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper uses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves numerical optimization, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
